## Local vs. On-chain Evidence

The generated dashboard uses a local demo prover until a real browser prover is
wired. Local proof output is useful for testing the encoding and interface, but
it must not be presented as live contract verification.

On-chain evidence remains unavailable by default. After a real Stellar
transaction succeeds, populate the typed `OnChainEvidence` object in the
generated dashboard with:

- network;
- verifier contract ID;
- transaction hash;
- ledger number;
- confirmation time;
- Stellar Expert transaction URL.

The explorer action is enabled only when that evidence is configured.

## Known Limitations

- The verifier relies on a testnet-only deployment of the UltraHonk base verifier.
